# Style Rules (TypeScript + React)

## General
- Keep changes small and scoped; avoid speculative abstraction.
- Follow existing naming and folder conventions before adding new patterns.
- Prefer explicit types at module boundaries (service contracts, storage contracts).

## React Components
- Keep presentational shared components in `src/components/ui`.
- Keep feature-specific components under `src/components/<feature>`.
- Avoid business side effects in reusable UI primitives.

## Services and Data
- API calls go through `src/services/api-client.ts`.
- Keep DTO/type definitions in `src/services/*/types.ts` or `src/services/types.ts`.
- Convert external responses in service/feature layers, not in route definitions.

## Validation
- Use Yup schemas in `src/features/<feature>/validation`.
- Validate form payloads before triggering async actions.

## Imports
- Use aliases (`@/*`, `@ui/*`) consistently.
- Keep import order stable: external libs, internal aliases, local relatives.
- Do not add new path aliases without strong need.

## Tests and Checks
- For behavior changes, run lint/tests relevant to touched modules.
- Do not start dev servers as part of verification unless explicitly requested.
